    <h1>About CalcPhi</h1>

    <p>CalcPhi is a financial tools publisher. We build free, accurate financial calculators wrapped in deep educational content, distributed across five English-speaking markets: India, USA, Canada, Australia, and UK.</p>

    <h2>Our Mission</h2>
    <p>Every financial calculator on CalcPhi exists to answer one question honestly: <em>what does this number actually mean for me?</em> We believe that access to accurate financial calculation should not require a financial advisor, a spreadsheet, or a subscription. Every tool on this site is permanently free.</p>

    <h2>Our Methodology</h2>
    <p>Every calculator on CalcPhi uses the correct underlying financial formula for the instrument — not approximations. Results are verified against:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>RBI guidelines and AMFI-published formulas for India calculators</li>
      <li>IRS and SEC standards for USA calculators</li>
      <li>Bank of Canada and CRA guidelines for Canada calculators</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Current rates (PPF interest rate, income tax slabs, FD rates) are updated every quarter to reflect the latest government notifications.</p>

    <h2>Editorial Standards</h2>
    <p>Each calculator page is reviewed for accuracy before publication and updated when underlying rules, rates, or tax structures change. We clearly label every page with the date of last update and the financial year or quarter to which the figures apply.</p>

    <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
    <p>CalcPhi calculators are for educational and estimation purposes only. Results are not financial advice. Consult a SEBI-registered financial advisor (India), SEC-registered advisor (USA), or equivalent regulated professional in your jurisdiction before making investment or financial decisions.</p>
    <p>Mutual fund investments are subject to market risks. Past returns do not guarantee future performance.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>For corrections, feedback, or partnership enquiries: <a href="/contact/">contact us here</a>.</p>
